cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with the study of register automata, which are a type of finite automata. Therefore, cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves complexity analysis and decision problems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of Ackermann function and the undecidability result indicate that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) could also be relevant sub-categories.
